President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 15, 2015 as America Recycles Day. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of recycling and reducing consumption in order to protect the environment for future generations. He highlights the significant impact recycling can have on conserving natural resources, reducing waste, generating jobs, and mitigating harmful emissions. The President calls on individuals, businesses, and governments to take action by recycling at home, establishing recycling programs, and implementing measures that make recycling easier for consumers. He urges the American people to observe this day with appropriate programs and activities, and to continue their efforts to reduce, reuse, and recycle throughout the year.